Sources: https://extensions.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/Extension/OpenID%20Connect/OpenID%20Connect%20Authenticator/ 


Yes, you can map additional user profile fields from your OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider to the XWiki user properties. This is done by using the `oidc.user.mapping` property in the `xwiki.properties` file. The `oidc.user.mapping` property defines a mapping between custom properties coming from the OIDC provider and the XWiki side.

Here's an example of how to map additional user profile fields:

```java
// Map myXproperty1 from the OpenID Connect provider to the XWiki userProfile
oidc.user.mapping=myxproperty1=${oidc.user.subject}

// Map myxproperty2 from the OpenID Connect provider to a prefixed form of oidc.user.subject in xwikiUserProperties
oidc.user.mapping=myxproperty2=myprefix-${oidc.user.subject}
```

In these mappings, replace `myXproperty1` and `myXproperty2` with the names of your custom user profile fields from the OIDC provider that you want to map. The `${oidc.user.subject}` part corresponds to the default user identifier in XWiki as generated by OpenID Connect (OIDC).

This mapping should be included under the `xwiki` section in the `xwiki.properties` file, which is typically located at `/etc/xwiki/xwiki-config/xwiki.properties`. You might need administrative access to edit this file.

Please ensure you follow your organization's policy regarding changes to system configurations and consult with your IT department if necessary before making any modifications.
